  "prompt": "What is pork gelatin?",
  "response": "Pork gelatin is a protein substance derived from the collagen found in pig skin, bones, and connective tissues. It is produced by boiling these parts of the pig and extracting the collagen, which is then dried and processed into a powder or sheets. Pork gelatin is commonly used in food production as a gelling agent, stabilizer, and thickener in products like desserts, marshmallows, candies, and some dairy products. It is also used in pharmaceuticals, cosmetics, and photography. For those who follow dietary restrictions based on religious or personal beliefs, it's important to note that pork gelatin is not considered halal or kosher.",
